# docs/
| `004-implementation-plan.md` | Stage 0 baseline → Stage 14 roll-out calendar. **Stages 1+2 = TB 2.0/2.1 + DeepSWE + custom long-horizon (primary evals); Stage 9 = SWE-bench Verified demoted to debug-only**. Each stage has contract, scope, rationale, exit criteria, rollback plan, benchmark artifact requirement. | living |
| `005-engine-binary-install.md` | **Round-6** one-page bootstrap for installing `llama-server.exe` / `ik_llama-server.exe` so the `qwen35-08b` profile actually has a backend. 3 install paths (scoop / prebuilt / from source), verification commands, fallback to ik_llama fork if upstream llama.cpp regressions. | accepted |

and self-improvement layer owned by `pheno-harness`).

## Reading order for a new agent

1. `../SPEC.md`
2. `../DESIGN.md`
3. `ARCHITECTURE_LAYERS.md` — layer contract: `forge-dev`,
   `omniroute-dev`, `pheno-serve-dev`, `PhenoLM`, engines, `bifrost`.
4. `GARDEN_LOOP.md` — managed self-improvement policy.
5. `PHENOLM_MIGRATION.md` — `pheno-specs` → `PhenoLM` migration,
   `agileplus-specs/` submodule handling.
6. `PUBLISHING.md` — split-repo publishing protocol.
7. `adrs/0001-current-state-audit.md` — read-only state snapshot,
   citations, unknowns.
8. `adrs/0003-local-serving-bootstrap.md` — local model workstream
   decision + bootstrap commands.
9. `specs/001-eval-architecture.md` — eval suite taxonomy, metric
   taxonomy, reproducibility contract, intent-graph design.
10. `specs/002-trace-evalset.md` — per-role trace-derived eval pipeline.
11. `specs/003-model-engine-matrix.md` — local 0.8B–35B × engine
    matrix, 3090 Ti vRAM budget, M1 Pro fallback, spec-dec zoo.
12. `specs/004-implementation-plan.md` — staged plan, ordered PRs,
    weekly roll-out.

## adrs/ — Architecture Decision Records

| ADR | Topic | Status |
|---|---|---|
| `0001-current-state-audit.md` | Read-only state snapshot, primary-source verification, gap analysis, unknowns. | accepted, last refresh 2026-07-03 |
| `0002-risks-register.md` | 20 named risks with detection + mitigation. | living |
| `0003-local-serving-bootstrap.md` | Local-first workstream **decision + bootstrap commands**. **No model SKUs asserted in this ADR** — picks live in `state/hf_scrape/2026-07-03/v2_shortlist.md` and are sign-off-gated by user. | revised |
| `0004-stale-sku-retrospective.md` | Root-cause analysis of the stale-Qwen-2.5 / stale-Qwen3-8B / missed-Gemma-4 chain. 6 control rules for future model picks, including the March-2026 recency cutoff. | accepted |
| `0005-locked-baseline-march-2026-cutoff.md` | Locked cloud baselines (7) + self-hosted (3) + March-2026 recency cutoff + b16/BitNet dropped + spec-dec zoo in scope + HF-token-handling rule. Single source of truth for what we evaluate. **Round 5 update:** Granite-4.0-H-Micro dropped per user 2026-07-04; Qwen3.5-0.8B serves dual-role as T0 + T1 small-task. | accepted |
| `0006-pheno-serve-dev-bootstrap.md` | Round-6 local-model-driven-item manifest: `pheno-serve-dev` started, smoke + probe captured, OpenRouter drift vs 2026-07-04 snapshot. **Gated behind** `llama-server.exe` install for the `qwen35-08b` profile to actually accept completions. | accepted |

## specs/ — Specifications

| Spec | Topic |
|---|---|
| `001-eval-architecture.md` | Eval suites, metric taxonomy, reproducibility contract, intent-graph layers A–E. |
| `002-trace-evalset.md` | Trace-derived per-role eval set, spec schema, replay executor. |
| `003-model-engine-matrix.md` | Model × engine matrix, vRAM budget, parallel sweep targets, spec-dec zoo. **No model SKUs asserted** — see `state/hf_scrape/2026-07-04/locked_shortlist.md` (locked picks from ADR 0005) or `state/hf_scrape/2026-07-03/v2_shortlist.md` (superseded round-3 shortlist). |
| `004-implementation-plan.md` | Stages (1 = TB driver, 2 = DeepSWE primary, 3 = Intent-graph A, 4 = perf suite, 5 = self-improvement, 6 = matrix sweep, 7 = trace per-role, 8 = Intent-graph B–E, 9 = SWE-bench Verified debug-only, 10 = Codex fork gated), ordered PRs, weekly roll-out. Cost per stage: `state/hf_scrape/2026-07-04/cost_projection.md`. |

## Top-level canonicals

- `../SPEC.md` — single-page specification.
- `../DESIGN.md` — single-page design intent.

## Live data sources (NOT docs, but referenced from the docs above)

**Current (2026-07-04) — locked picks per ADR 0005:**

- `../state/hf_scrape/2026-07-04/locked_shortlist.md` — single source of truth for what we evaluate. 7 cloud baselines (Granite-4.0-H-Micro dropped) + 3 self-hosted (Qwen3.5 0.8B serves as both T0 drafter and T1 small-task tier) + recency stamps + OR + HF pricing cross-ref.
- `../state/hf_scrape/2026-07-04/cost_projection.md` — per-stage run-cost projection (TB 2.0/2.1, DeepSWE primary, SWE-bench Verified demoted) with token-budget assumptions and `n_attempts` sensitivity.
- `../state/hf_scrape/2026-07-04/locked_shortlist.json` — machine-readable form.
- `../state/hf_scrape/2026-07-04/models.jsonl` — 11 records (8 cloud + 3 self-hosted) with canonical IDs + OR + HF data.
- `../state/hf_scrape/2026-07-04/or_api_snapshot.json` — raw OpenRouter `/api/v1/models` response for the 8 cloud picks.
- `../state/hf_scrape/2026-07-04/last_modified_probes.json` — HF last-modified dates for recency stamps.

**Historical (2026-07-03) — superseded, kept for traceability:**

- `../state/hf_scrape/2026-07-03/v2_shortlist.md` — round-3 capability-first shortlist (superseded by 2026-07-04 locked_shortlist).
- `../state/hf_scrape/2026-07-03/author_flagships.json` — round-3 author-flagship probe.
- `../state/hf_scrape/2026-07-03/models.jsonl` — 260-model baseline corpus (kept records from the unauthenticated 2026-07-03 sweep).

**Scripts (re-runnable):**

- `../scripts/hf_round4_locked.py` — round-4 locked-pick scraper (OR + HF).
- `../scripts/hf_round4_followups.py` + `hf_round4_followups_v2.py` — Ornith / Liquid / Qwen canonical-id probes.
- `../scripts/hf_round4_last_modified.py` — HF last-modified-date probes.
- `../scripts/hf_list_families.py` — fast family-existence probe.
- `../scripts/hf_scrape_2026_07_03.py` — round-3 baseline corpus scraper.

These files are referenced from the docs and the live eval loop, but
they are **state, not docs**.

## Conventions

- ADRs are immutable once accepted; corrections go in a follow-up ADR.
- Specs are versioned by spec number; v2 of a spec supersedes v1.
- Docs never embed secrets. Any secret reference uses an env-var name
  only, never a value.
- `*.manifest.json` files (from `../specs/001-eval-architecture.md`
  §6) are committed; result JSONs are gitignored.
